
The Vim handbook

basics

left h
down j
up k
right l

Word deletion: place cursor the the beginning of the word
and  type dw


Move to beginning of sentence 0

Delete a whole line  dd

Replace character: go with the cursor to tht characher , 
type r nd then type character you want

:w write
:wq write and quit
:q! quit and dont save

:u undo
Ctrl + R redo

PASTE
i) place cursor at begin
ii) V for lines
iii) y
iv) p to paste after cursor


SEARCH case insensitive
:set ignore case
/your_word and then Enter
n for next occurence N for previous

Move between tabs
Ctrl + w ,w


